The '''North American Association for Experiential Education''' (NAAEE) is a US-based nonprofit organization working to “bring the brightest minds together to accelerate environmental literacy and [[Civic_engagement | civic engagement]] through the power of [[Education | education]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://naaee.org/about-us/mission-and-vision|title=Mission and Vision|date=19 May 2015|website=Naaee.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref>

The organization was founded in 1971 in the U.S. as the National Association for Environmental Education<ref name="naaee.org">{{cite web|url=https://cdn.naaee.org/sites/default/files/naaeehistory2001.pdf|format=PDF|title=Thirty years of History 1971 to 2001|website=Naaee.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> but now includes members from over 30 countries.<ref name="naaee.org"/><ref name="naaee.org1">{{cite web|url=https://naaee.org/about-us|title=About Us|date=19 May 2015|website=Naaee.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref>  

NAAEE and its 56 affiliate organizations<ref>{{cite web|url=https://naaee.org/our-partners/affiliates|title=Affiliates|date=19 May 2015|website=Naaee.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> in the US, Canada, Mexico have over 16,000 members;<ref name="naaee.org1"/> additional affiliates exist outside North America in Asia and Oceania.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://naaee.org/our-partners/international|title=International|date=19 May 2015|website=Naaee.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> These partners, many of whom operate at a state or provincial level, have their own conferences, publications, or other activities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e3washington.org|title=E3 WA Home Page|website=E3Washington.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nacee.org|title=nacee|website=Nacee.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://taee.org|title=Texas Association for Environmental Education|website=Taee.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://minnesotaee.org|title=MAEE – Minnesota Association for Environmental Education|website=Minnesotaee.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref>

NAAEE holds its own annual conference,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/naaee-annual-conference/2240196065996236/|title=NAAEE Annual Conference|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> supports teacher training in [[Environmental_education | environmental education]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.epa.gov/epa/newsreleases/epa-awards-108m-national-environmental-education-training-program.html|title=EPA Awards $10.8M for National Environmental Education Training Program - US EPA|first=US|last=EPA,OA,OEAEE,OMR|website=Archive.epa.gov|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> supports research demonstrating the impact of environmental education,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://publicgardens.org/events/eeworks-demonstrating-power-environmental-education|title=eeWORKS: Demonstrating the Power of Environmental Education - American Public Gardens Association|website=Publicgardens.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> and produces a wide variety of publications, including ''Guidelines for Excellence''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eeao.org/index.php/guidelines-for-excellence|title=Environmental Education Association of Oregon - Guidelines for Excellence|website=Eeao.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.plt.org/alignment-to-standards/national/naaee-guidelines|title=NAAEE Excellence in EE - Guidelines for Learning|website=Plt.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> in environmental education.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.epa.gov/education/environmental-education-ee-publications|title=Environmental Education (EE) Publications - US EPA|website=Epa.gov|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref>

The Natural Start Alliance,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://naturalstart.org|title=Natural Start - In early childhood, learning comes naturally|website=Naturalstart.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> a project of NAAEE, works to connect young children with nature.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eeinwisconsin.org/resource/about.aspx?s=111841.0.0.2209|title=Environmental Education in Wisconsin - Natural Start: An Early Childhood EE Website|website=Eeinwisconsin.org|accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref>

